cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and texture analysis. The use of kernel methods also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The mention of metrics on the manifold suggests that it could also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. The use of SVM and kernel PCA further supports the Machine Learning (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the mention of Diffusion Tensor Imaging (DTI) segmentation suggests that it could also belong to the Data Science (cs.DS) sub-category.
